{"name":"Std.Internal.UV","instances":[{"typeNames":["Std.Internal.UV.Timer"],"name":"Std.Internal.UV.instNonemptyTimer","className":"Nonempty"}],"imports":["Init.System.IO","Init.System.Promise"],"declarations":[{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/Std/Internal/UV.lean#L105-L113","name":"Std.Internal.UV.Timer.stop","line":105,"kind":"opaque","docLink":"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer.stop","doc":"This function has different behavior depending on the state of the `Timer`:\n- If it is initial or finished this is a no-op.\n- If it is running the execution of the timer is stopped and it is put into the finished state.\n  Note that if the last `IO.Promise` generated by `next` is unresolved and being waited\n  on this creates a memory leak and the waiting task is not going to be awoken anymore.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer.stop\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">UV</span>.<span class=\"name\">Timer</span>.<span class=\"name\">stop</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(timer : <a href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer\">Timer</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO\">IO</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/Std/Internal/UV.lean#L94-L103","name":"Std.Internal.UV.Timer.reset","line":94,"kind":"opaque","docLink":"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer.reset","doc":"This function has different behavior depending on the state and configuration of the `Timer`:\n- If it is initial or finished this is a no-op.\n- If it is running and `repeating` is `false` this will delay the resolution of the timer until\n  `durationMs` milliseconds after the call of this function.\n- Delay the resolution of the next tick of the timer until `durationMs` milliseconds after the\n  call of this function, then continue normal ticking behavior from there.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer.reset\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">UV</span>.<span class=\"name\">Timer</span>.<span class=\"name\">reset</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(timer : <a href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer\">Timer</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO\">IO</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/Std/Internal/UV.lean#L75-L92","name":"Std.Internal.UV.Timer.next","line":75,"kind":"opaque","docLink":"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer.next","doc":"This function has different behavior depending on the state and configuration of the `Timer`:\n- if `repeating` is `false` and:\n  - it is initial, run it and return a new `IO.Promise` that is set to resolve once `durationMs`\n    milliseconds have elapsed. After this `IO.Promise` is resolved the `Timer` is finished.\n  - it is running or finished, return the same `IO.Promise` that the first call to `next` returned.\n- if `repeating` is `true` and:\n  - it is initial, run it and return a new `IO.Promise` that resolves right away\n    (as it is the 0th multiple of `durationMs`).\n  - it is running, check whether the last returned `IO.Promise` is already resolved:\n     - If it is, return a new `IO.Promise` that resolves upon finishing the next cycle\n     - If it is not, return the last `IO.Promise`\n     This ensures that the returned `IO.Promise` resolves at the next repetition of the timer.\n  - if it is finished, return the last `IO.Promise` created by `next`. Notably this could be one\n    that never resolves if the timer was stopped before fulfilling the last one.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer.next\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">UV</span>.<span class=\"name\">Timer</span>.<span class=\"name\">next</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(timer : <a href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer\">Timer</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO\">IO</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/System/Promise.html#IO.Promise\">IO.Promise</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a>)</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/Std/Internal/UV.lean#L64-L73","name":"Std.Internal.UV.Timer.mk","line":64,"kind":"opaque","docLink":"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer.mk","doc":"This creates a `Timer` in the initial state and doesn't run it yet.\n- If `repeating` is `false` this constructs a timer that resolves once after `durationMs`\n  milliseconds, counting from when it's run.\n- If `repeating` is `true` this constructs a timer that resolves after multiples of `durationMs`\n  milliseconds, counting from when it's run. Note that this includes the 0th multiple right after\n  starting the timer. Furthermore a repeating timer will only be freed after `Timer.stop` is called.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">UV</span>.<span class=\"name\">Timer</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(timeout : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt64\">UInt64</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(repeating : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO\">IO</a> <a href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer\">Timer</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/Std/Internal/UV.lean#L60-L60","name":"Std.Internal.UV.instNonemptyTimer","line":60,"kind":"instance","docLink":"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.instNonemptyTimer","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.instNonemptyTimer\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">UV</span>.<span class=\"name\">instNonemptyTimer</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nonempty\">Nonempty</a> <a href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer\">Timer</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/Std/Internal/UV.lean#L47-L58","name":"Std.Internal.UV.Timer","line":47,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer","doc":"`Timer`s are used to generate `IO.Promise`s that resolve after some time.\n\nA `Timer` can be in one of 3 states:\n- Right after construction it's initial.\n- While it is ticking it's running.\n- If it has stopped for some reason it's finished.\n\nThis together with whether it was set up as `repeating` with `Timer.new` determines the behavior\nof all functions on `Timer`s.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">UV</span>.<span class=\"name\">Timer</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/Std/Internal/UV.lean#L37-L41","name":"Std.Internal.UV.Loop.alive","line":37,"kind":"opaque","docLink":"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.alive","doc":"Checks if the event loop is still active and processing events.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.alive\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">UV</span>.<span class=\"name\">Loop</span>.<span class=\"name\">alive</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/Std/Internal/UV.lean#L31-L35","name":"Std.Internal.UV.Loop.configure","line":31,"kind":"opaque","docLink":"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.configure","doc":"Configures the event loop with the specified options.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.configure\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">UV</span>.<span class=\"name\">Loop</span>.<span class=\"name\">configure</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(options : <a href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options\">Loop.Options</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/Std/Internal/UV.lean#L29-L29","name":"Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options.blockSigProfSignal","line":29,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options.blockSigProfSignal","doc":"Block a SIGPROF signal when polling for new events. It's commonly used for unnecessary wakeups\nwhen using a sampling profiler.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options.blockSigProfSignal\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">UV</span>.<span class=\"name\">Loop</span>.<span class=\"name\">Loop</span>.<span class=\"name\">Options</span>.<span class=\"name\">blockSigProfSignal</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(self : <a href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options\">Options</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/Std/Internal/UV.lean#L23-L23","name":"Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options.accumulateIdleTime","line":23,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options.accumulateIdleTime","doc":"Accumulate the amount of idle time the event loop spends in the event provider.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options.accumulateIdleTime\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">UV</span>.<span class=\"name\">Loop</span>.<span class=\"name\">Loop</span>.<span class=\"name\">Options</span>.<span class=\"name\">accumulateIdleTime</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(self : <a href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options\">Options</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/Std/Internal/UV.lean#L19-L19","name":"Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options.mk","line":19,"kind":"ctor","docLink":"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options.mk","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">UV</span>.<span class=\"name\">Loop</span>.<span class=\"name\">Loop</span>.<span class=\"name\">Options</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(accumulateIdleTime blockSigProfSignal : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options\">Options</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/Std/Internal/UV.lean#L16-L29","name":"Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options","line":16,"kind":"structure","docLink":"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options","doc":"Options for configuring the event loop behavior.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/UV.html#Std.Internal.UV.Loop.Loop.Options\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">UV</span>.<span class=\"name\">Loop</span>.<span class=\"name\">Loop</span>.<span class=\"name\">Options</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>"}]}